<tr id="L293"><td><a href="#L293">293</a></td><td>LWAXANA:  I've been looking forward to meeting you, Dara.</td></tr>

<tr id="L294"><td><a href="#L294">294</a></td><td>TIMICIN:  Whatever you have to say to me, can be said in front of her.</td></tr>

<tr id="L295"><td><a href="#L295">295</a></td><td>DARA:  I see. Father, come home. This is wrong.</td></tr>

<tr id="L296"><td><a href="#L296">296</a></td><td>TIMICIN:  Dara, if I could show you the work I have begun. There's still so much for me to do.</td></tr>

<tr id="L297"><td><a href="#L297">297</a></td><td>DARA:  There's nothing for me to look at. It is irrelevant.</td></tr>

<tr id="L298"><td><a href="#L298">298</a></td><td>LWAXANA:  Your father's work may save your world, my dear. I would hardly consider that irrelevant.</td></tr>

<tr id="L299"><td><a href="#L299">299</a></td><td>DARA:  All I'm concerned with now is you, not your work. Your work is over. It is your time to rest.</td></tr>

<tr id="L300"><td><a href="#L300">300</a></td><td>LWAXANA:  Perhaps you will feel differently as you get a little older, say approaching sixty.</td></tr>

<tr id="L301"><td><a href="#L301">301</a></td><td>DARA:  My father taught me to cherish The Resolution. I don't know how you have poisoned him to reject it.</td></tr>

<tr id="L302"><td><a href="#L302">302</a></td><td>LWAXANA:  It's an obscene ritual.</td></tr>

<tr id="L303"><td><a href="#L303">303</a></td><td>DARA:  How dare you. How dare you criticize my way of life, my beliefs.</td></tr>

<tr id="L304"><td><a href="#L304">304</a></td><td>TIMICIN:  Please. Please, Dara. Please.</td></tr>

<tr id="L305"><td><a href="#L305">305</a></td><td>DARA:  Where will you go?</td></tr>

<tr id="L306"><td><a href="#L306">306</a></td><td>TIMICIN:  I don't know.</td></tr>

<tr id="L307"><td><a href="#L307">307</a></td><td>DARA:  And where will you die? I cannot bear the thought of you being laid to rest on some other world. That you will not lie beside my mother. That I will not be able to lie beside you when my Resolution comes. I'm sorry. I don't know how you can go on with your life knowing that each day you live is an insult to everything we believe in. Father, I love you. But I am ashamed.</td></tr>

<tr id="L308"><td><a href="#L308">308</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Dara leaves</td></tr>

<tr id="L309"><td><a href="#L309">309</a></td><td>TIMICIN:  I would like to be alone now, please.</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Lwaxana's quarters</td></tr>
<tr id="L310"><td><a href="#L310">310</a></td><td>LWAXANA:  I am suddenly suddenly not sure of myself. It's a feeling I'm not at all used to. I don't think I like it very much, little one.</td></tr>

<tr id="L311"><td><a href="#L311">311</a></td><td>TROI:  Not sure of yourself?</td></tr>

<tr id="L312"><td><a href="#L312">312</a></td><td>LWAXANA:  My life has been full. Now and then, perhaps it's overflowed a little, but I enjoy living. And now I am asking myself is it possible I was wrong to encourage Timicin to choose life?</td></tr>

<tr id="L313"><td><a href="#L313">313</a></td><td>TROI:  You were honest with him, Mother. You had to be.</td></tr>

<tr id="L314"><td><a href="#L314">314</a></td><td>LWAXANA:  Maybe I want him to live just to keep me company.</td></tr>

<tr id="L315"><td><a href="#L315">315</a></td><td>TROI:  Of course you do. But you didn't do this for yourself, you did it for him.</td></tr>

<tr id="L316"><td><a href="#L316">316</a></td><td>LWAXANA:  Did I? Then look what I've done to him. He's like a man who's lost his faith. I never considered how deeply ingrained this Resolution liturgy is.</td></tr>

<tr id="L317"><td><a href="#L317">317</a></td><td>TROI:  Ritual provides a structure in society, good rituals and bad rituals alike.</td></tr>

<tr id="L318"><td><a href="#L318">318</a></td><td>LWAXANA:  Well, this is a bad one.</td></tr>

<tr id="L319"><td><a href="#L319">319</a></td><td>TROI:  Your point of view.</td></tr>

<tr id="L320"><td><a href="#L320">320</a></td><td>LWAXANA:  It should be the point of view of any reasonably intelligent middle-aged person. Unfortunately, it is not.</td></tr>

